<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) Models</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <div class="intro">
            <p>''Designed by Allan, Stella, Martha, Isaiah, Michael''</p>
        </div>
        <section class="model">
            <h2>Waterfall Model</h2>
            <img src="https://www.ishir.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/waterfall-scaled.jpg" alt="Waterfall Model">
            <p>The Waterfall Model is a linear sequential flow where progress is seen as flowing steadily downwards (like a waterfall) through phases.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="model">
            <h2>Agile Model</h2>
            <img src="https://hackr.io/blog/media/agile-image-2-min.png" alt="Agile Model">
            <p>The Agile Model emphasizes iterative development and collaboration between self-organizing cross-functional teams.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="model">
            <h2>V-Model</h2>
            <img src="https://d12zh9bqbty5wp.cloudfront.net/images/f9e66e179b6747ae54108f82f8ade8b3c25d76fd30afde6c395822c530196169-1676405018298.png" alt="V-Model">
            <p>The V-Model, or Validation and Verification Model, extends the waterfall model by emphasizing the importance of testing at each development stage.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="model">
            <h2>Iterative Model</h2>
            <img src="https://files.codingninjas.in/article_images/iterative-model-0-1646848405.webp" alt="Iterative Model">
            <p>The Iterative Model focuses on repetition of phases and refinement of deliverables through multiple iterations.</p>
        </section>
        <section class="model">
            <h2>Spiral Model</h2>
            <img src="https://www.sitesbay.com/software-engineering/images/spiral-model.png" alt="Spiral Model">
            <p>The Spiral Model combines iterative development with the systematic aspects of the waterfall model, emphasizing risk assessment.</p>
        </section>
    </main>
